# 📚 Academic Task - User Registration with Express.js

📄 Description
Academic task using **Node.js** and **Express.js** that registers users (name, email, and password) in an in-memory list through an HTML form (POST) and dynamically displays the list with JavaScript.


# 🚀 Features
- HTML page for user registration.  
- Data sent to the server via **POST**.  
- Users stored in an **in-memory list**.  
- Dynamic rendering of the user list with **JavaScript (script.js)**.  


# 📂 Project Structure
📦 express-users-project
┣ 📜 server.js # Express server
┣ 📜 index.html # User registration and listing page
┣ 📜 script.js # Dynamic rendering logic
┗ 📜 README.md # Project documentation


# 🛠️ Technologies Used
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)  
- [Express.js](https://expressjs.com/)  
- HTML5  
- JavaScript  


# ▶️ How to Run the Project

1. Clone this repository:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/express-users-project.git

Install dependencies: npm install

Start the server: node src/server.js

Open in your browser: http://localhost:3000

# 👨‍🎓 Note
This project was developed for academic purposes as a practical exercise to learn basic web development concepts with Node.js, Express.js, and dynamic integration with JavaScript.